New Records: Kyle Tucker reached 101 RBIs, leading the American League in the category, marking his second consecutive season with over 100 RBIs.
Key Match Events: The Astros scored five runs in the fifth inning to rally from a 4-1 deficit and take a 7-4 lead.
Jurickson Profar hit a two-run home run and three hits for the Padres.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Astros were struggling at home with a 36-35 record at Minute Maid Park.
